This checks freqOfFreq.size()==1, but the original code checked freq.size()==1 (i.e., only one distinct value in the window).

These are not the same thing. freqOfFreq.size()==1 means all distinct values currently share the same frequency, which can happen even when there are multiple distinct values — e.g., window [1,2], both appear once: freq = {1:1, 2:1}, freqOfFreq = {1:2}, size 1. This window has two distinct values each appearing once — that should require both f and 2f (frequencies 1 and 2) to be present, but only frequency 1 exists. By the problem rules this is not balanced, yet your code marks it as balanced and updates best.

